+ltilib                            % base directory
|-+src                             % all source files of the LTI-Lib
| |                                % are here
| |-+basics                        % basic types and classes
| |-+math                          % mathematical types and algorithms
| |-+imgProc                       % image processing algorithms
| |-+ioBasics                      % general input/output interfaces
| |-+io                            % input/output functors
| | |-+jpeg                        %   modified implementation of png
| | |-+png                         %   and jpeg loaders from J. Miano
| |-+system                        % threads, mutex and other system
| |                                %   dependend stuff
| |-+classifiers                   % some classifiers
| |-+viewer                        % visualization functors
|
|-+data                            % some algorithms require data
|                                  %   special data files, that will
|                                  %   be stored here.
|
|
|-+bin                             % the executables will be stored here
|-+lib                             % the libraries (*.lib *.dll)
|
|-+doc                             % documentation for the LTI-Lib
| |-+homepage                      % html sources for the homepage
| |-+html                          % generated html documentation will
| |                                %   be left here
| |-+src                           % general documentation files with
| |                                %   Doxygen comments 
| |-+styleguide                    % the programmers style guide
| | |-+en                          % english
| | |-+de                          % german (deprecated)
|
|-+obj                             % the object files will be stored
| |                                %   here.
| |-+debug                         % for the debug version
| |-+release                       % for the release version
| |-+profile                       % for the profiling version
|
|-+tester                          % some default test programs
| |--ltiTester.cpp and other tools
|
|-+linux                           % linux specific stuff (maybe this
| |                                %   works under other unix plattforms
| |-+Makefile,Dependencies
| |-+workbench                     % before new functors become part
| |                                %   of the lib., they can be tested
| |                                %   here
| |-+g++                           % some missing files in gcc 2.95.x
|
|-+win                             % windows specific stuff
| |-+console                       % console application
| |-+buildLib                      % project to construct the library
| |-+batchFiles                    % some tools to construct the lib.
|
|-+misc                            % other stuff
| |-+lamath                        % some class wrappers for lapack
| |                                %   functions
| |-+java                          % java/jni interfaces for the ltilib
|   |-+jni                         % C/C++ JNI source code
|   |-+sources                     % the Java source tree
|   |-+classes                     % the Java class tree 
|   |-+lib                         % the generated shared libraries
|   |-+docs                        % the doc files generated by JavaDoc
|
|-+tools                           % some tools
| |-+perl                          % perl scripts
|   |--ltiGenerator and templates  % functor generator
|
|-+examples                        % some examples using the ltilib
| |-+template                      % Makefile used in the examples
| |-+bitmap2eps                    % convert a bitmap (jpeg,png,bmp)
| |                                %   into an eps file.
| |-+collage                       % make an image collage
| |-+colorquat                     % color quantization
| |-+distort                       % geometrically distort and deform images 
| |-+fader                         % fade images
| |-+ltiview                       % small viewer application using
| |                                %   the LTI-Lib viewer class.
| |-+secucam                       % use the ToUCam Philips webcam in a
| |                                %   simple motion detection tool
| |-+setgen                        % generation of a 2D point set for
| |                                %   training of classifiers
